This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with biomedical image analysis and proposes a new deep learning architecture for segmentation tasks. It also uses a convolutional neural network for skin cancer classification. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

The use of dermoscopic images and benchmark datasets from the International Skin Imaging Collaboration 2018 (ISIC-2018) suggests that this paper could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. 

Finally, the use of deep learning models for segmentation and classification tasks suggests that this paper could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
